<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="319" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1510,2005]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1763,1789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[712,897,1763,1789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref28371" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 17, 1 - 208." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[755,813,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
this species belonged to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1838" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Mithracinae">Mithracinae</taxonomicName>
, which was raised recently to family 
<taxonomicName authority="(Windsor &amp; Felder 2014)" authorityName="Windsor &amp; Felder" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Windsor &amp; Felder" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[638,1072,1799,1825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mithracidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Mithracidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Windsor, A. M. &amp; Felder, D. L." box="[788,1064,1799,1825]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="145 - 173" refId="ref32862" refString="Windsor, A. M. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2014) Molecular phylogenetics and taxonomic reanalysis of the family Mithracidae McLeay (Decapoda: Brachyura: Majoidea). Invertebrate Systematics, 28, 145 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 13011" type="journal article" year="2014">Windsor &amp; Felder 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, some genera, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Miers" authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1879" box="[195,440,1835,1861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Macrocoeloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[195,363,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Macrocoeloma</emphasis>
Miers
</taxonomicName>
, were removed from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Windsor &amp; Felder" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[684,819,1835,1861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mithracidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mithracidae</taxonomicName>
based on molecular phylogenetics (12S, 16S and COI mitochondrial genes) and a morphological re-examination. This genus is now considered an 
<emphasis box="[1200,1356,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">incertae sedis</emphasis>
group, closely related to other 
<taxonomicName authority="(Windsor &amp; Felder 2014)" authorityName="Windsor &amp; Felder" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Windsor &amp; Felder" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[417,829,1907,1933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Epialtidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Windsor, A. M. &amp; Felder, D. L." box="[546,821,1907,1933]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="145 - 173" refId="ref32862" refString="Windsor, A. M. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2014) Molecular phylogenetics and taxonomic reanalysis of the family Mithracidae McLeay (Decapoda: Brachyura: Majoidea). Invertebrate Systematics, 28, 145 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 13011" type="journal article" year="2014">Windsor &amp; Felder 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. As the position of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1049,1211,1907,1933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Macrocoeloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis box="[1049,1072,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1087,1211,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">laevigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not well defined, we decided to follow the classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[620,799,1943,1969]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref28371" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 17, 1 - 208." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[661,710,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
and retained it in the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Samouelle" authorityYear="1819" box="[1123,1219,1943,1969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Majidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
